Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    apt-get update && \
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        curl \
        jq \
        tar \
        gzip \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # Install pytest for the later test-runner environment
    pip install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial filesystem state expected by the assignment/tests
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Create the data directory and populate the two required files
    mkdir -p /home/user/data

    # file_a.txt  (content: "Alpha\n")
    printf 'Alpha\n' > /home/user/data/file_a.txt

    # file_b.txt  (content: "Beta\n")
    printf 'Beta\n' > /home/user/data/file_b.txt

    # Ensure permissive permissions so the runtime (non-root) user
    # has full access to everything under /home/user.
    chmod -R a+rwX /home/user

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author backup-training-setup

%help
    Container image that provides the initial state for the backup-automation
    exercise:
      • /home/user/data/file_a.txt   (contains "Alpha\\n")
      • /home/user/data/file_b.txt   (contains "Beta\\n")
    No /home/user/backups directory is present; the student’s script will
    create it and the resulting artefacts. Pytest is pre-installed for the
    automated checks.